description: From Middle English amoven, ameven, from Old French amover.

verbs.description: amove (third-person singular simple present amoves, present participle amoving, simple past and past participle amoved)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To set in motion; to stir up, excite.

verbs.description: amove (third-person singular simple present amoves, present participle amoving, simple past and past participle amoved)

entries.meaning: To remove (a person or thing) from a position.
(law) To dismiss from an office or station.
